## # Resource: splunk.InputsTcpCooked

Create or update cooked TCP input information and create new containers for managing cooked data.


{{% examples %}}
## Example Usage

{{< chooser language "typescript,python,go,csharp" / >}}

{{% example csharp %}}
```csharp
using Pulumi;
using Splunk = Pulumi.Splunk;

class MyStack : Stack
{
    public MyStack()
    {
        var tcpCooked = new Splunk.InputsTcpCooked("tcpCooked", new Splunk.InputsTcpCookedArgs
        {
            ConnectionHost = "dns",
            Disabled = false,
            RestrictToHost = "splunk",
        });
    }

}
```
